x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>That&#8217;s been quoted so many times that it=
&#8217;s lost its meaning. &#8220;Yeah, yeah, technology can be really cool=
=2E I get it.&#8221; Personally, when I r=
ead it, I think about the technology=
 itself, but that&#8217;s not the important part. </span><strong>The import=
ant part is the magical experience a sufficiently advanced technology makes=
 people feel.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Here&#8217;s what I mean in an exa=
mple. Sending a rocket into space with people on it and bringing them back =
to Earth safely, is, at least to my non-rocket scientist brain, indistingui=
shable from magic. But the technology itself wasn&#8217;t nearly as magical=
 as watching, two months into COVID lockdowns, SpaceX and NASA send humans =
to space from American soil for the first time in nearly a decade.&#160;</p=
><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7e009c1c-ca13-4857-a93e-e14ec53ec=
b19?r=3D9p0gt" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"youtube-wrap" style=3D"display: b=
